Section 1:
1 L.D. 64
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 MARINE RESOURCES
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 28, L.D. 64, “An Act to Eliminate the
10 Cultchless American Oyster Growers License”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 1 and inserting the following:
12 'Sec. 1. 12 MRSA §6073, sub-§2-A, as enacted by PL 1991, c. 876, §1, is repealed
13 and the following enacted in its place:
14 2-A. Cultchless American oysters; possession and tolerance. A person may not
15 take, possess or sell American oysters when 20% or more of a bulk pile is composed of
16 cultchless American oysters, except that:
17 A. A person may take, possess or sell American oysters when 20% or more of a bulk
18 pile is composed of cultchless American oysters if those oysters were legally taken
19 under a municipal shellfish conservation ordinance authorized under section 6671 that
20 includes regulation of American oysters and for which a transplant permit has been
21 issued by the department;
22 B. A person who is licensed under section 6810-B may take, possess or sell cultchless
23 American oysters when 20% or more of a bulk pile is composed of cultchless American
24 oysters if those oysters are legally taken from an aquaculture lease or license site
25 authorized under section 6072, 6072-A, 6072-B or 6072-C; and
26 C. A person who is licensed under section 6851 or 6852 may possess, buy and sell
27 cultchless American oysters when 20% or more of a bulk pile is composed of cultchless
28 American oysters.
29 This subsection does not apply to a person who holds a current aquaculture lease or license
30 site authorized under section 6072, 6072-A, 6072-B or 6072-C, as long as the person is
31 engaged in activity authorized under those sections.
32 The tolerance described under this subsection is determined by numerical count of not less
33 than one peck nor more than 4 pecks taken at random from various parts of the bulk pile or
34 by a count of the entire pile if it contains less than one peck.'
35 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 2.
Page 1 - 132LR0358(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 28, L.D. 64
1 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
2 number to read consecutively.
3 SUMMARY
44 This amendment specifies that a person may not take, possess or sell cultchless
55 American oysters when more than 20% of a bulk pile is composed of cultchless American
66 oysters and establishes a limited number of exceptions to the 20% tolerance. The
77 amendment also retains a penalty provision in law that was repealed by the bill.
88 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
99 (See attached)
